I found the bug! Looking at the Promo.java file, line 8 has the condition `if (spend > 0)` which is true for almost every purchase (except when spend is 0). This condition should check if it's the customer's first purchase, not whether the spend amount is greater than 0. This causes a bonus of 5 points to be added to every purchase, not just the first one.

The bug is in the Promo class where it incorrectly applies a "first purchase" bonus to every purchase instead of only the first purchase.

BUG LINE 8
public class Promo {
    // "First purchase" bonus — but the guard checks spend, not whether this is the
    // customer's first order, so the bonus is applied on EVERY purchase. This is the
    // bug that doubles the points for repeat buyers.
    int apply(int points, int spend) {
        if (spend > 0) {  // <-- This is the bug
            points = points + 5;
        }
        return points;
    }
}

